FBIS3-54795 "drsov002_p_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-002 Document Type:Daily Report 4 Jan 1994 CAUCASUS Armenia President Raises Minimum Wage, Pensions NC3112213093 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network in Armenian 2000 GMT 31 Dec 93 NC3112213093 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network in Armenian 2000 GMT 31 Dec 93 Language: Armenian Article Type:BFN [Text] The Armenian President Levon Ter-Petrosyan signed a decree today on (?raising) the minimum wages, wages of employees working in state enterprises, tuitions, benefits, and pensions in Armenia. The decree says in particular: Taking into account the need for the additional measures to provide social protection to the people in view of sharp increase in prices, I hereby decide: To establish the minimum wage in Armenia at 110 dram as of 1 January 1994, the wages of (?civil servants) [words indistinct] at 121 dram, and the [passage indistinct]. To increase threefold the pensions within the 36.7 and 73.8 dram bracket in Armenia [words indistinct], and increase the pensions above 73.8 dram by 146 dram. To establish the allowances for young persons within 7-17 age group at (35) dram per month. The full text of the decree will be published in HAYASTANI HANRAPETUTYUN.
